definition: geographic latitude (i.e. angle between the equatorial plane and the normal to the reference ellipsoid)
-ly/structural particle: used before a verb or adjective, linking it to preceding modifying adverbial adjunct
texture/grain (of wood)/inner essence/intrinsic order/reason/logic/truth/science/natural science (esp. physics)/to manage/to pay attention to/to run (affairs)/to handle/to put in order/to tidy up
to pass/to spend (time)/measure/limit/extent/degree of intensity/degree (angles, temperature etc)/kilowatt-hour/classifier for events and occurrences

sentences.english: The geographic latitude lower, the stearic acid content higher.
sentences.chinese: 地理緯度低，其硬脂酸含量高。

sentences.english: Each point on Earth is specified by geographic latitude and longitude.
sentences.chinese: 地球上每一點都可以用地理緯度和經度來確定。

sentences.english: So, usually each additional 15 degrees latitude, exposure should increase the half-file.
sentences.chinese: 所以，通常地理緯度每增加15度，曝光應增加半檔。
